The 24/7 OSS combines more features than is offered by any other semiauto pistol on the market, and it has an entirely new trigger mechanism that completely eliminates two of the longest-standing problems with double-action and double-action-only pistol design. When you take up the slack in the new Taurus PT 24/7 OSS pistol trigger, you’ve got a first-shot pull that’s as short and quick as a standard single-action Government Model 1911. And for every following shot, the trigger returns to the same fast, short-pull position. No more long, mushy trigger pulls on the first shot then transitioning to a short pull on the second shot, as is the case with conventional double-action autoloaders.

Moreover, if the gun fails to fire, the 24/7 OSS mechanism automatically and instantly resets to a conventional double-action long-pull position and allows you to pull the trigger again–just like a double-action revolver–without needing to manually manipulate the slide. Essentially, it’s a single-action pistol that becomes a double action in an emergency.

title: For Sale:  Yugo SKS Model 59/66A1
postcontent:
For sale is a Yugo SKS Model 59/66A1 chambered for 7.62x39 in very good condition.  It has the Yugo grenade launcher which is ported to also serve as a compensator as well as the Yugo night sights.  It has the Yugo recoil pad on the buttstock and the blade bayonet which is in excellent shape.  It holds ten rounds in its box magazine.  There are some signs of use including a small scratch on the receiver cover and some fading of the bluing here and there, but there's no rust or pitting.  The stock has some dings here and there, but there are no cracks.  It's overall condition is very good compared to most of the milsurp SKSs you see out there.  The serial numbers of the receiver, box magazine, and the bolt match.  The serial number of the stock does not match.  It does not have the toolkit in the stock, but it does have the cleaning rod.  It might not be the most collectible SKS, but it is definitely a shooter.  Yugo SKSs are known for being very well made at the Zastava factory with their milled receivers.  I can tell you it shoots better than all the Chinese SKSs I have ever owned.  The only reason I'm selling it is because I recently acquired another Yugo SKS in even better condition.  I'm also throwing in a handful of corrosive milsurp ammo and some stripper clips.  

Price is $400.  Face to face sales only in NWA. Must be an Arkansas resident of legal age to purchase this firearm and not have any legal restrictions from owning it. I will require that you sign a bill of sale acknowledging this. If you refuse to sign, then no sale. This will be a deal breaker with me.
